---
/**
 * src/pages/about.astro — About page
 */

import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn more about this Astro template — what's included and how to use it."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">About</h1>

    <div class="prose-content mt-8">
      <p>
        This is a production-ready Astro template designed to give you a
        solid foundation for content-driven websites, personal blogs, and
        documentation sites.
      </p>

      <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Astro</strong> — Static site generator with island
          architecture and zero-JS by default.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>TypeScript</strong> — Full type safety across all components,
          pages, and content collections.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Tailwind CSS</strong> — Utility-first CSS with dark mode
          support via the <code>class</code> strategy.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>MDX</strong> — Write blog posts in Markdown with the option
          to embed interactive JSX components.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Content Collections</strong> — Type-safe content with Zod
          schema validation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Sitemap</strong> — Auto-generated <code>sitemap.xml</code>{' '}
          for SEO.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>RSS</strong> — Auto-generated RSS feed at{' '}
          <code>/rss.xml</code>.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Deployment</h2>
      <p>
        The template is pre-configured for deployment on{' '}
        <a href="https://netlify.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Netlify
        </a>
        . Connect your Git repository and Netlify will automatically build and
        deploy on every push to <code>main</code>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Security headers (X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, CSP, etc.)
        are configured in <code>netlify.toml</code>.
      </p>

      <h2>CMS Integration</h2>
      <p>
        The template includes a <code>cloudcannon.config.yml</code> for
        <a href="https://cloudcannon.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          CloudCannon
        </a>
        CMS, giving editors a visual interface to manage blog posts and pages
        without touching the code.
      </p>

      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Clone or fork the repository.</li>
        <li>Run <code>npm install</code>.</li>
        <li>Run <code>npm run dev</code> and open <code>http://localhost:4321</code>.</li>
        <li>Edit <code>astro.config.mjs</code> and set your <code>site</code> URL.</li>
        <li>Add blog posts to <code>src/content/blog/</code>.</li>
        <li>Deploy to Netlify by connecting your Git repo.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
